        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(state): write state atomically to prevent corruption on termination",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Fixes non-atomic Lobster state writes by staging JSON to a sibling temp file, fsyncing it, then renaming it over the target.\n- Routes `writeStateJson`, `state.set`, SDK `stateSet`, and SDK `writeState` through atomic replacement.\n- Preserves existing state-file modes across replacement and creates new state files as `0600`.\n- Removes sibling temp files on failed write, close, chmod, or rename paths.\n- Keeps approval-index exclusive-create semantics unchanged.\n\n## Linked context\n\nCloses #108.\nCloses #109.\n\n## Maintainer repair\n\nThis branch was refreshed onto current `main` and the ClawSweeper findings were addressed:\n\n- Existing file modes are preserved in both helper copies.\n- New state files are private by default.\n- Temp files are cleaned up on every failed path after staging begins.\n- Added tests for atomic read/write behavior, mode preservation, private new-file modes, and failed-replacement cleanup in both store and SDK paths.\n- Added an Unreleased changelog entry thanking @KrasimirKralev.\n\n## Proof\n\nLocal verification on macOS, Node from repo toolchain:\n\n```text\npnpm run typecheck\npass\n\nnode --test dist/test/state.test.js dist/test/resume.test.js dist/test/multi_approval_resume.test.js dist/test/approve_preview.test.js\npass: 14/14\n\npnpm run lint\npass: 0 errors, existing warnings only\n\npnpm run test\npass: 242/242\n```\n\nReal built SDK proof outside the test harness:\n\n```text\nLOBSTER_STATE_DIR=<tmp> node --input-type=module <script importing ./dist/src/sdk/primitives/state.js>\n{\"readBack\":{\"ok\":true,\"n\":2},\"firstMode\":\"600\",\"secondMode\":\"600\"}\n```\n\nThat proof writes state through the built SDK, replaces it, reads it back, and confirms the file remains private before and after replacement.\n\nAutoreview:\n\n```text\n/Users/steipete/Projects/agent-scripts/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main\nautoreview clean: no accepted/actionable findings reported\noverall: patch is correct (0.84)\n```\n",
